# =============================================================================
# Operator Credentials - LOCAL ONLY
# =============================================================================
# These credentials are used for provisioning and automation (creating Azure
# app registrations, Cloudflare tunnels, Portainer stacks, GitHub secrets).
#
# NEVER commit this file. It is gitignored.
# These are YOUR operator credentials, not the app's runtime secrets.
#
# Copy this file to .operator.env and fill in the values.
#
# ALL SECTIONS ARE OPTIONAL. If you don't have API credentials for a service,
# the setup guide will walk you through the manual alternative (dashboard UI,
# portal, etc.) instead.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Portainer API Access (OPTIONAL)
# Used for creating and managing stacks via the Portainer API.
# If you don't have these, the setup guide will walk you through creating
# stacks manually in the Portainer UI.
#
# To get an API key:
#   1. Log into Portainer
#   2. Click your username (bottom-left) or go to My Account
#   3. Scroll to Access Tokens
#   4. Click Add Access Token
#   5. Copy the token (it won't be shown again)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
PORTAINER_PROD_URL=
PORTAINER_PROD_API_KEY=
PORTAINER_DEV_URL=
PORTAINER_DEV_API_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare API Access (OPTIONAL)
# Used for creating tunnels and DNS entries via API.
# If you don't have these, the setup guide will walk you through creating
# tunnels manually in the Cloudflare Zero Trust dashboard, or you can just
# provide the tunnel token and hostname directly.
#
# Create an API token at https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens
# with Zone:DNS:Edit and Account:Cloudflare Tunnel:Edit permissions.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Azure CLI and GitHub CLI
# These tools use their own authentication flows:
#   Azure:  az login
#   GitHub: gh auth login
# No credentials need to be stored here for these tools.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
